          <p></p>
          
          
            <p>Hemant Kaushik is a television journalist with eight years of experience. From Sri Lanka to Bangladesh and from record-breaking games like World Cups and Commonwealth Games to match-fixing scams and controversies, Hemant has covered a wide spectrum. He was honoured with the Best Sports Reporter Award by the Government of Uttarakhand.</p>
            <p>He has produced many documentaries on sports and current affairs and was a member of Aaj Tak channel’s award winning Vande Mataram series on India's war history. </P>
            <p>Hemant has a Master’s degree in Mass Communication from Hissar University in 2013 and has a Post Graduate Programme in TV Reporting, News Production and Copy Writing in 2005 from TV Today Media Institute. Currently Hemant is working at ITMI as Faculty.</p>
            <p>In his free time Hemant likes to read and listen music. He is also a passionate traveller and loves to explore new sites.</p>

      
      
